                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During an informal luncheon meeting following the first session of the Nine-Power
                    Conference, <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> discussed the possible <pb facs="0346"
                        n="1414" xml:id="pg_1414"/> stationing of British troops in Austria after
                    their withdrawal from Trieste, United States plans to negotiate a mutual
                    security treaty with Formosa, and the problem of ensuring that the Suez Canal
                    remain open to all traffic. Summaries of the discussion of these three subjects
                    were transmitted to the Department of State in telegrams <gloss
                        target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 7, 8, and 9, respectively; none are printed
                    here. (Conference files, lot 60 D 627, CF 379)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
